Sound-Activated Lamp

Description
An electronic circuit that detects sound signals using an op-amp and activates a relay to turn on a lamp.

Components
- Op-Amp LM741  
- Transistor (NPN)  
- Relay Module  
- Microphone  
- Power Supply  

Features
- Amplifies audio signal and converts it to DC  
- Triggers relay when sound intensity crosses threshold  
- Demonstrates analog-to-digital decision making with op-amp  
